                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" htag="li" hclass="sense" id="angloirishwar_sng_1"><span class="sensetop" hclass="sensetop" htag="span"><span class="def" hclass="def" htag="span">the formal name for the <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/the-troubles#the_troubles_topg_1" title="Troubles definition"><span class="ndv">Troubles</span></a> in Northern Ireland between 1919 and 1921. It involved violent fighting between the <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/ira" title="IRA definition"><span class="ndv">IRA</span></a> and the <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/the-black-and-tans#the_black_and_tans_topg_1" title="Black and Tans definition"><span class="ndv">Black and Tans</span></a> and was brought to an end by the <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/the-anglo-irish-treaty#the_anglo_irish_treaty_topg_1" title="Anglo-Irish Treaty definition"><span class="ndv">Anglo-Irish Treaty</span></a>, which recognized the <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/establishment#establishment_sng_3" title="establishment definition"><span class="ndv">establishment</span></a> of the independent Republic of Ireland.</span></span>    <div id="ring-links-box">
